## Finding: Missing Phase 0 → Phase 1 Handoff Artifact

### Gap Type: MISSING_HANDOFF
### Severity: HIGH
### Evidence: Phase 0 has 15 skills that each produce their own artifacts (health report, architecture diagrams, debt register, incident history, infrastructure map, etc.). But there is NO skill that SYNTHESIZES these into a Phase 0 Exit Artifact — a single document that Phase 1 can consume. Phase 1 skills (client_discovery, idea_to_spec, competitive_analysis) each assume certain context exists, but they have no standardized input from Phase 0. The transition from "understanding the system" to "brainstorming what to build next" has no bridge. A developer finishing Phase 0 has 5-10 separate documents and no clear summary of "here's what we know, here's where we stand, here are the constraints on what we can build."
### Proposed Resolution: Create a `phase_exit_summary` skill or add a mandatory "Phase 0 Exit Checklist" template that synthesizes key findings into: (1) System health score, (2) Top 3 risks, (3) Business constraints, (4) Technical constraints, (5) Team velocity baseline, (6) Recommended next actions. This artifact is the explicit INPUT to Phase 1.
### Cross-Phase Impact: Without a Phase 0 exit artifact, Phase 1 brainstorming is unanchored. Teams may brainstorm features that contradict existing technical constraints or underestimate the debt burden.

================================================================

## Finding: Missing Existing Metrics Instrumentation Inventory

### Gap Type: MISSING_SKILL
### Severity: MEDIUM
### Evidence: Phase 1's product_metrics skill asks teams to define their North Star metric and AARRR framework. But it never asks: "What metrics are ALREADY being tracked? What analytics platform is in use? What events are already instrumented?" A team joining a project may discover in Phase 1 that they are designing a metrics strategy for a system that already has Mixpanel, 200 custom events, and a defined North Star — they just didn't know it. Phase 0 has NO skill that inventories existing analytics/metrics instrumentation. infrastructure_audit covers monitoring (Datadog, CloudWatch) but not product analytics (Mixpanel, Amplitude, PostHog, Segment).
### Proposed Resolution: Add an "Analytics & Metrics Instrumentation" section to either codebase_health_audit or infrastructure_audit. Document: analytics platform in use, events currently tracked, dashboards that exist, who owns the analytics configuration. Output feeds directly into Phase 1's product_metrics skill.
### Cross-Phase Impact: Phase 1 product_metrics will waste time designing metrics that already exist. Phase 5 (Ship) metrics verification has no baseline.

================================================================

## Finding: User Persona Context Missing from Phase 0

### Gap Type: MISSING_HANDOFF
### Severity: MEDIUM
### Evidence: Phase 1's user_research skill starts each research cycle from scratch — defining user segments, recruitment criteria, and assumptions. But for an EXISTING product, user personas likely already exist (in old PRDs, customer support tickets, marketing docs, or just in team members' heads). Phase 0 has no skill that extracts and documents existing user persona knowledge. When team_knowledge_transfer interviews departing developers, it focuses on system knowledge — not user/customer knowledge. The "oral tradition capture" in team_knowledge_transfer doesn't explicitly surface user mental models or customer segment definitions.
### Proposed Resolution: Add a "User & Customer Context" section to team_knowledge_transfer or project_context. Capture: existing user segments, known pain points, customer success patterns, support ticket themes, and any existing persona documentation. This directly populates Phase 1's user_research baseline.
### Cross-Phase Impact: Phase 1 user_research will repeatedly rediscover knowledge that the team already had. Phase 1 client_discovery skips this if working on existing products.

================================================================

## Finding: No Skill Ensures Local Dev Environment Readiness

### Gap Type: MISSING_SKILL
### Severity: HIGH
### Evidence: codebase_navigation mentions "Can a new dev build in <30 minutes?" as one item in codebase_health_audit step 5 (Build Health). But no skill ACTUALLY WALKS THROUGH the local development environment setup and verifies it works. A new developer cannot use ANY other Phase 0 skill (architecture_recovery, codebase_health_audit, system_design_review) if they cannot run the project locally. This is the most immediate practical blocker and it is buried as a single checkbox in a 105-line audit skill. There is no "Developer Environment Setup" skill that: checks prerequisites, walks through setup steps, identifies common failure points, and verifies the environment is working.
### Proposed Resolution: Create a `dev_environment_setup` skill (Phase 0). Trigger: "Set up local development", "Get the project running", "New developer setup". Scope: Prerequisites check, dependency installation, environment variables setup (.env.example walkthrough), database seeding, test run verification, and common failure points with solutions. This is the FIRST skill any new developer should run.
### Cross-Phase Impact: Blocking for ALL other Phase 0 skills. A developer who cannot run the project locally cannot audit health, recover architecture, or assess tech debt with confidence.

