## Finding: Missing Multi-Cloud & Hybrid Infrastructure Patterns

### Gap Type: FAILURE_MODE_UNCOVERED
### Severity: MEDIUM
### Evidence: infrastructure_audit is built around single-cloud (AWS-centric) deployments. The skill references ECS, Lambda, S3, EBS, CloudFormation — AWS terminology exclusively. In 2026, hybrid (on-prem + cloud) and multi-cloud architectures are common in enterprise contexts. Additionally, edge computing deployments (Cloudflare Workers, Vercel Edge, Lambda@Edge) and serverless-native architectures require fundamentally different audit approaches. A developer auditing a Cloudflare Workers + Durable Objects + R2 stack using the infrastructure_audit skill would find ~40% of the skill irrelevant and have no guidance for the other 60%.
### Proposed Resolution: Add deployment topology variants to infrastructure_audit: (A) Single-cloud (current), (B) Multi-cloud, (C) Hybrid on-prem+cloud, (D) Serverless-native, (E) Edge-native. Each variant should have adapted checklists for its specific resources and cost models.
### Cross-Phase Impact: Phase 5 (Ship) deployment patterns assume cloud infrastructure exists. Phase 7 (Maintenance) monitoring assumes cloud-native monitoring tools.

