## Finding: No Skill Addresses Multi-Repo (Polyrepo) Architecture

### Gap Type: FAILURE_MODE_UNCOVERED
### Severity: MEDIUM
### Evidence: All Phase 0 navigation and architecture skills assume a SINGLE REPOSITORY. architecture_recovery's dependency graph works within one repo. codebase_navigation's "First 30 Minutes" process starts at a single README. But many enterprise systems are polyrepo: the backend API is one repo, the frontend is another, infrastructure-as-code is a third, shared libraries are in a fourth. A developer onboarding to this system needs to: identify all the repos that constitute "the system", understand cross-repo dependency management (npm packages, git submodules, artifact registries), and map the full system across multiple codebases. No skill addresses how to navigate or audit a multi-repo system.
### Proposed Resolution: Add a "Multi-Repo System Mapping" step to architecture_recovery. When multiple repos are detected: (1) Identify all repos that form the system, (2) Map cross-repo dependencies (APIs, shared packages, event contracts), (3) Identify the "system of record" repo for infrastructure and deployment. Produce a cross-repo architecture map.
### Cross-Phase Impact: Phase 3 (Build) changes may require coordinated changes across multiple repos. Phase 5 (Ship) deployment may require coordinated releases. Without a cross-repo map, this coordination fails.

